What is ABC's degree of formalization and centralization? ABC Corporation is highly standardized and centralized. Formalization refers to the degree of standardization and documenting of an organization's procedures and processes. Every employee's job description at ABC Corporation has been meticulously prepared and is unchanging. This suggests that the organization is highly formalized, since personnel are required to adhere to a precise set of rules and procedures. Centralization refers to the degree to which an organization's decision-making power is concentrated at the highest levels. In ABC Corp., everyone reports to the CEO via a few supervisors, and low-level workers have little decision-making ability. This suggests that the organization is highly centralized, since decision-making authority is concentrated at the highest levels. 